But just one quick question--

Trucks don't use inner tubes anymore--
99.9/10ths of them all all 11 x 22.5 tubeless--
10 x 20's tube type tires went out 15 years ago--

Why not simply use rubber electrical hole type grommets ??

Pop them into the hole--they fit snug, and won't pop out--and will
support the fuel line just ducky--

Works OK for me anyway.

